template of sorts.

00:07:45.160 --> 00:07:46.750 align:middle line:84%
Or is trying to
find its way back

00:07:46.750 --> 00:07:48.445 align:middle line:90%
to a state of balance or yeah.

00:07:48.445 --> 00:07:51.010 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: We all need
to do that, yeah.

00:07:51.010 --> 00:07:53.080 align:middle line:84%
But let's say you have
a serious injury where

00:07:53.080 --> 00:07:55.510 align:middle line:84%
you're losing a lot of blood
or you've had an amputation

00:07:55.510 --> 00:07:58.330 align:middle line:84%
or you've been in a
severe car accident,

00:07:58.330 --> 00:08:00.130 align:middle line:90%
you go into a state of shock.

00:08:00.130 --> 00:08:03.460 align:middle line:84%
And this level of
consciousness says, the facts

00:08:03.460 --> 00:08:05.800 align:middle line:84%
don't much match
my understanding.

00:08:05.800 --> 00:08:09.070 align:middle line:84%
This person I'm inhabiting
here should be intact.

00:08:09.070 --> 00:08:10.210 align:middle line:90%
And that's not the case.

00:08:10.210 --> 00:08:10.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The were
missing a toenail.

00:08:10.870 --> 00:08:11.410 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: So I leave.

00:08:11.410 --> 00:08:12.210 align:middle line:90%
I leave.

00:08:12.210 --> 00:08:14.710 align:middle line:84%
So a level of consciousness
leaves the body briefly.

00:08:14.710 --> 00:08:17.950 align:middle line:84%
And so the person will say,
I'm OK, when they're not.

00:08:17.950 --> 00:08:19.690 align:middle line:84%
And that's the key
note of arnica.

00:08:19.690 --> 00:08:24.158 align:middle line:84%
So that's a deeper understanding
of that remedy than someone

00:08:24.158 --> 00:08:26.200 align:middle line:84%
who just thinks, oh, this
will help me to repair.

00:08:26.200 --> 00:08:28.617 align:middle line:84%
When the soul is pulled back--
this level of consciousness

00:08:28.617 --> 00:08:30.760 align:middle line:84%
is pulled back into
the body, healing

00:08:30.760 --> 00:08:33.230 align:middle line:84%
is much more possible
than when it's not there.

00:08:33.230 --> 00:08:35.409 align:middle line:84%
And so that's why
arnica actually works.

00:08:35.409 --> 00:08:37.548 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because it
helps pull that portion

00:08:37.548 --> 00:08:38.590 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: It pulls that--

00:08:38.590 --> 00:08:40.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that's why
it's used-- which I just

00:08:40.590 --> 00:08:43.645 align:middle line:84%
learned very recently-- is used
for emotional trauma as well.

00:08:43.645 --> 00:08:45.400 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: Because
in emotional trauma,

00:08:45.400 --> 00:08:47.470 align:middle line:84%
when you think that a state of
shock is an emotional trauma--

00:08:47.470 --> 00:08:48.595 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, absolutely.

00:08:48.595 --> 00:08:51.590 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: We are not able to
process some kinds of shock.

00:08:51.590 --> 00:08:54.053 align:middle line:84%
If you're watching a murder
or you're in a car which that

00:08:54.053 --> 00:08:56.470 align:middle line:84%
would completely flipped over
or if you've gotten a really

00:08:56.470 --> 00:09:00.930 align:middle line:84%
serious injury, you cannot
possibly process that

00:09:00.930 --> 00:09:01.730 align:middle line:90%
at the moment.

00:09:01.730 --> 00:09:04.430 align:middle line:84%
So we are designed so that
we go into a state of shock

00:09:04.430 --> 00:09:07.000 align:middle line:84%
so that later on we
can deal with it.

00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:10.240 align:middle line:84%
If you meet somebody who goes
in who's feeling like that,

00:09:10.240 --> 00:09:12.160 align:middle line:84%
you say, wow, that's
a really strong person

00:09:12.160 --> 00:09:13.180 align:middle line:90%
said nothing happened.

00:09:13.180 --> 00:09:14.440 align:middle line:90%
Everything's OK.

00:09:14.440 --> 00:09:15.340 align:middle line:90%
That's not accurate.

00:09:15.340 --> 00:09:16.240 align:middle line:90%
They're in a state of shock.

00:09:16.240 --> 00:09:16.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:09:16.480 --> 00:09:17.770 align:middle line:90%
They're in that numb place.

00:09:17.770 --> 00:09:18.220 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: You're right.

00:09:18.220 --> 00:09:19.480 align:middle line:84%
If you meet them
a few weeks later

00:09:19.480 --> 00:09:20.830 align:middle line:84%
and then they're
starting to process it

00:09:20.830 --> 00:09:22.330 align:middle line:84%
and they're weeping
and wailing, you

00:09:22.330 --> 00:09:24.190 align:middle line:90%
don't say, oh, what a weakling.

00:09:24.190 --> 00:09:25.180 align:middle line:90%
They can't handle this?

00:09:25.180 --> 00:09:25.990 align:middle line:90%
You don't do that.

00:09:25.990 --> 00:09:29.290 align:middle line:84%
But basically, you
heal when your soul

00:09:29.290 --> 00:09:32.500 align:middle line:84%
is completely in your
body when you're grounded

00:09:32.500 --> 00:09:35.140 align:middle line:84%
and when this level of
consciousness is fully there.

00:09:35.140 --> 00:09:36.400 align:middle line:90%
And that's what arnica does.

00:09:36.400 --> 00:09:38.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, that's profound.

00:09:38.380 --> 00:09:40.150 align:middle line:84%
Much more profound
than taking care of--

00:09:40.150 --> 00:09:42.053 align:middle line:90%
I take it for dental work.

00:09:42.053 --> 00:09:44.470 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: Well when you're
having significant dental work,

00:09:44.470 --> 00:09:45.940 align:middle line:84%
a little bit of
that is going on.

00:09:45.940 --> 00:09:47.170 align:middle line:84%
You're a little bit
out of your body.

00:09:47.170 --> 00:09:47.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:09:47.470 --> 00:09:49.300 align:middle line:90%
And it actually helps very much.

00:09:49.300 --> 00:09:50.810 align:middle line:90%
I find it helps a lot.

00:09:50.810 --> 00:09:53.960 align:middle line:84%
So OK, now that we've kind
of gotten a couple of the pop

00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:56.200 align:middle line:84%
things on the table,
let's start getting

00:09:56.200 --> 00:09:57.850 align:middle line:90%
into the story a little bit.

00:09:57.850 --> 00:10:00.820 align:middle line:84%
And what I was so
interested and reading

00:10:00.820 --> 00:10:03.010 align:middle line:84%
"Sane Asylums" was
looking at where

00:10:03.010 --> 00:10:05.980 align:middle line:84%
we are right now compared to
where this kind of healing

00:10:05.980 --> 00:10:07.240 align:middle line:90%
was once upon a time.

00:10:07.240 --> 00:10:08.040 align:middle line:90%
And especially--

00:10:08.040 --> 00:10:09.660 align:middle line:84%
I live in Sacramento,
California.

00:10:09.660 --> 00:10:12.540 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things that
many, many cities have seen

00:10:12.540 --> 00:10:17.160 align:middle line:84%
is a much higher incidence of
homelessness and encampments,

00:10:17.160 --> 00:10:19.560 align:middle line:84%
where people are sleeping
out in the cold everywhere

00:10:19.560 --> 00:10:20.730 align:middle line:90%
under every overpass.

00:10:20.730 --> 00:10:23.430 align:middle line:84%
They're everywhere just
trying to find some place

00:10:23.430 --> 00:10:26.340 align:middle line:84%
to stay out of the wind
and the rain with people

00:10:26.340 --> 00:10:29.910 align:middle line:84%
ranting and people
on drugs trying

00:10:29.910 --> 00:10:31.980 align:middle line:90%
to self-soothe and alcohol.

00:10:31.980 --> 00:10:33.870 align:middle line:90%
And there's no place for them.

00:10:33.870 --> 00:10:36.420 align:middle line:84%
Well, they're trying to
build big places actually.

00:10:36.420 --> 00:10:39.750 align:middle line:84%
But right now, it's so
overwhelming the mental health

00:10:39.750 --> 00:10:43.050 align:middle line:84%
crisis and there's
nowhere for them to go.

00:10:43.050 --> 00:10:45.030 align:middle line:84%
There's no one
looking after them.

00:10:45.030 --> 00:10:46.920 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing in place.

00:10:46.920 --> 00:10:49.860 align:middle line:84%
How do you see that
as someone that

00:10:49.860 --> 00:10:53.945 align:middle line:84%
does what you do with such
great care for a living?

00:10:53.945 --> 00:10:55.570 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: Well, that's
a huge question.

00:10:55.570 --> 00:10:58.810 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the homeless do have
a lot of mental health issues.

00:10:58.810 --> 00:11:00.203 align:middle line:90%
That's true.

00:11:00.203 --> 00:11:01.870 align:middle line:84%
I will tell you that
in my own practice,

00:11:01.870 --> 00:11:04.180 align:middle line:84%
and people getting
are presenting

00:11:04.180 --> 00:11:06.760 align:middle line:84%
as sicker and sicker
because of an epidemic

00:11:06.760 --> 00:11:10.420 align:middle line:84%
of autoimmune conditions because
of the effects of the drugs

00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:12.520 align:middle line:90%
that people are on.

00:11:12.520 --> 00:11:13.630 align:middle line:90%
People are sicker.

00:11:13.630 --> 00:11:16.210 align:middle line:84%
And so it's harder for us
homeopaths to deal with them.

00:11:16.210 --> 00:11:18.668 align:middle line:84%
And there's always the risk of
they're regressing and going

00:11:18.668 --> 00:11:22.180 align:middle line:84%
back to their drugs because
they don't heal quickly enough

00:11:22.180 --> 00:11:23.540 align:middle line:90%
and we have to detox them.

00:11:23.540 --> 00:11:25.990 align:middle line:84%
So back to your question,
what we fantasize about

00:11:25.990 --> 00:11:30.610 align:middle line:84%
is having an asylum where we
can have people 24 hours a day

00:11:30.610 --> 00:11:32.988 align:middle line:84%
and take care of them
so that we can get them

00:11:32.988 --> 00:11:34.780 align:middle line:84%
through those crises
and not lose them back

00:11:34.780 --> 00:11:36.550 align:middle line:90%
to the conventional means.

00:11:36.550 --> 00:11:41.000 align:middle line:84%
There's a real need for
asylum care for people.

00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:44.500 align:middle line:84%
But this is an era
that's quite bygone.

00:11:44.500 --> 00:11:46.000 align:middle line:90%
Basically now we drug people up.

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:46.857 align:middle line:90%
We do the opposite.

00:11:46.857 --> 00:11:48.940 align:middle line:84%
We send them back to their
community like zombies,

00:11:48.940 --> 00:11:53.800 align:middle line:84%
and we relinquish
our opportunity

00:11:53.800 --> 00:11:56.170 align:middle line:84%
to work with them to grapple
with their mental illness

00:11:56.170 --> 00:11:57.753 align:middle line:84%
at the level of what
used to be called

00:11:57.753 --> 00:12:00.670 align:middle line:84%
moral hygiene, intense
discussions with people,

00:12:00.670 --> 00:12:02.200 align:middle line:84%
listening to them
very carefully.

00:12:02.200 --> 00:12:04.900 align:middle line:84%
The nurses at the
Middletown Hospital

00:12:04.900 --> 00:12:08.350 align:middle line:84%
that I write about under the
direction of Clara Barrus

00:12:08.350 --> 00:12:09.850 align:middle line:90%
were just paragons.

00:12:09.850 --> 00:12:11.290 align:middle line:90%
They were amazing people.

00:12:11.290 --> 00:12:12.130 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yes.

00:12:12.130 --> 00:12:13.560 align:middle line:84%
We're going to get
into her story.

00:12:13.560 --> 00:12:14.560 align:middle line:90%
Amazing people.

00:12:14.560 --> 00:12:15.400 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: She's a
lot to talk about.

00:12:15.400 --> 00:12:16.442 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, there is.

00:12:16.442 --> 00:12:19.480 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: And we would love
to have some places that we

00:12:19.480 --> 00:12:22.600 align:middle line:84%
can care take people so that
we can work with them long term

00:12:22.600 --> 00:12:24.280 align:middle line:90%
and not lose them.

00:12:24.280 --> 00:12:25.780 align:middle line:84%
So there's a number
of reasons why

00:12:25.780 --> 00:12:28.420 align:middle line:84%
we would like to have
facilities like that again.

00:12:28.420 --> 00:12:30.700 align:middle line:84%
And they could be staffed
by nurses, acupuncturists,

00:12:30.700 --> 00:12:32.005 align:middle line:90%
the pastors, chaplains.

00:12:32.005 --> 00:12:33.250 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:12:33.250 --> 00:12:34.750 align:middle line:84%
Especially nurses,
much overlooked.

00:12:34.750 --> 00:12:35.440 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: Yes.

00:12:35.440 --> 00:12:35.950 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:35.950 --> 00:12:36.310 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:36.310 --> 00:12:38.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And really,
some of the people-- well,

00:12:38.410 --> 00:12:40.270 align:middle line:84%
certainly
historically-- that were

00:12:40.270 --> 00:12:43.210 align:middle line:84%
key to the healing processes
of people in the day,

00:12:43.210 --> 00:12:45.040 align:middle line:90%
it was nurses, really.

00:12:45.040 --> 00:12:48.235 align:middle line:84%
And so I just want to go off of
one thing you said right now,

00:12:48.235 --> 00:12:50.110 align:middle line:84%
these days you're seeing
more and more people

00:12:50.110 --> 00:12:51.160 align:middle line:90%
with autoimmune problems.

00:12:51.160 --> 00:12:53.080 align:middle line:90%
I have to ask you this.

00:12:53.080 --> 00:12:56.620 align:middle line:84%
All around the world, we've
had global vaccine programs

00:12:56.620 --> 00:12:59.170 align:middle line:84%
where we've gotten all different
mish mashes of vaccines.

00:12:59.170 --> 00:13:03.370 align:middle line:84%
Has this had anything to do with
the change in our biochemistry

00:13:03.370 --> 00:13:06.310 align:middle line:84%
or the functioning of our
immune system that you can see?

00:13:06.310 --> 00:13:07.810 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: Well, I'm
afraid so, yeah.

00:13:07.810 --> 00:13:08.805 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Just across the board?

00:13:08.805 --> 00:13:09.930 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: Across the board.

00:13:09.930 --> 00:13:10.953 align:middle line:90%
People--

00:13:10.953 --> 00:13:12.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're
now getting into--

00:13:12.370 --> 00:13:13.570 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: It's a
troubling problem.

00:13:13.570 --> 00:13:15.612 align:middle line:84%
I mean, vaccinations are
the dysfunctional cousin

00:13:15.612 --> 00:13:17.232 align:middle line:84%
of homeopathy to
put it very mildly.

00:13:17.232 --> 00:13:18.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Explain that.

00:13:18.190 --> 00:13:19.180 align:middle line:90%
What is a vaccine?

00:13:19.180 --> 00:13:22.510 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: I mean, a
vaccine works basically

00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:25.030 align:middle line:84%
on the idea of using to
like to prevent like.

00:13:25.030 --> 00:13:28.280 align:middle line:84%
You get a small dose of cowpox
so that you don't get smallpox.

00:13:28.280 --> 00:13:30.580 align:middle line:84%
That's the law of similars
that homeopaths work on.

00:13:30.580 --> 00:13:34.390 align:middle line:84%
And the first vaccine by
Jenner, which the word vax comes

00:13:34.390 --> 00:13:38.620 align:middle line:84%
from cow was to give people
a small dose of cowpox,

00:13:38.620 --> 00:13:41.050 align:middle line:84%
which prevented them from
getting a more serious illness.

00:13:41.050 --> 00:13:43.990 align:middle line:84%
That was inoculation and pretty
close to how homeopathy works,

00:13:43.990 --> 00:13:47.530 align:middle line:84%
except homeopathy when
they made that medicine,

00:13:47.530 --> 00:13:48.730 align:middle line:90%
made it much more dilute.

00:13:48.730 --> 00:13:52.360 align:middle line:84%
So the big difference is,
vaccines are one-size-fits-all.

00:13:52.360 --> 00:13:54.550 align:middle line:84%
No matter who you
are, how old you are,

00:13:54.550 --> 00:13:55.930 align:middle line:90%
you get the same darn thing.

00:13:55.930 --> 00:13:57.138 align:middle line:90%
And also much too much of it.

00:13:57.138 --> 00:13:59.097 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, that's
what I was going to say.

00:13:59.097 --> 00:14:00.575 align:middle line:84%
It's not like a
diluted compound.

00:14:00.575 --> 00:14:02.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: So when
you dilute something,

00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:05.170 align:middle line:84%
you're actually going through
the process of making it

00:14:05.170 --> 00:14:08.215 align:middle line:84%
of matching you
as an individual,

00:14:08.215 --> 00:14:09.340 align:middle line:90%
whether when you practice--

00:14:09.340 --> 00:14:10.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Versus
actually infecting you.

00:14:10.930 --> 00:14:11.710 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:11.710 --> 00:14:13.502 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: The acupuncturists
and homeopaths

00:14:13.502 --> 00:14:14.800 align:middle line:90%
have this experience in common.

00:14:14.800 --> 00:14:17.710 align:middle line:84%
Someone will show up
and say, oh, Jerry I

00:14:17.710 --> 00:14:18.880 align:middle line:90%
fall between all the cracks.

00:14:18.880 --> 00:14:20.290 align:middle line:90%
I just don't fit any category.

00:14:20.290 --> 00:14:21.350 align:middle line:90%
What can you do for me?

00:14:21.350 --> 00:14:23.950 align:middle line:84%
And I always say, well, to a
homeopath, everyone's a crack.

00:14:23.950 --> 00:14:25.585 align:middle line:90%
We want to work on individually.

00:14:25.585 --> 00:14:27.460 align:middle line:84%
We're not interested in
putting you in a box.

00:14:27.460 --> 00:14:30.830 align:middle line:84%
Your diagnosis does
not define you.

00:14:30.830 --> 00:14:33.680 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, homeopathy
is the functional--

00:14:33.680 --> 00:14:35.680 align:middle line:84%
I would say the functional
cousin of the vaccine

00:14:35.680 --> 00:14:38.660 align:middle line:84%
is that you get a much,
much smaller amounts of what

00:14:38.660 --> 00:14:39.460 align:middle line:90%
matches you.

00:14:39.460 --> 00:14:41.810 align:middle line:84%
And that can prevent
another kind of a problem.

00:14:41.810 --> 00:14:44.455 align:middle line:84%
And it's perfectly matched--
should be ideally matched

00:14:44.455 --> 00:14:46.830 align:middle line:84%
to what's going on with you
at the mental, emotional, and

00:14:46.830 --> 00:14:48.025 align:middle line:90%
physical level.

00:14:48.025 --> 00:14:49.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you should
theoretically not

00:14:49.800 --> 00:14:51.550 align:middle line:84%
have any of these side
effects or problems

00:14:51.550 --> 00:14:55.300 align:middle line:84%
with a society of people with
plummeting immune systems.

00:14:55.300 --> 00:14:57.950 align:middle line:84%
That should not be coming
out of homeopathy that's not.

00:14:57.950 --> 00:14:58.600 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: Absolutely not.

00:14:58.600 --> 00:14:59.070 align:middle line:90%
That cannot happen.

00:14:59.070 --> 00:14:59.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That cannot happen.

00:14:59.830 --> 00:15:00.100 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: No.

