00:32:00.410 --> 00:32:02.840 align:middle line:84%
So the feeling of it's not
just a mechanical thing

00:32:02.840 --> 00:32:03.980 align:middle line:90%
being falling forward.

00:32:03.980 --> 00:32:06.530 align:middle line:84%
When you deconstruct it or
you do some excavation of it,

00:32:06.530 --> 00:32:09.840 align:middle line:84%
you find it has its roots in
a problem like being put down.

00:32:09.840 --> 00:32:12.110 align:middle line:84%
So for a child, for an
infant being put down

00:32:12.110 --> 00:32:15.470 align:middle line:84%
face down in the crib may
mean-- not for every child--

00:32:15.470 --> 00:32:17.390 align:middle line:84%
but it may mean an
existential crisis

00:32:17.390 --> 00:32:19.700 align:middle line:90%
like I'm going to be separated.

00:32:19.700 --> 00:32:21.950 align:middle line:84%
And separation anxiety
is part of that.

00:32:21.950 --> 00:32:24.305 align:middle line:84%
That remedy does not come
up very much for adults.

00:32:24.305 --> 00:32:26.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:32:26.150 --> 00:32:29.360 align:middle line:84%
So you almost have to be
a psychiatrist, a psychic.

00:32:29.360 --> 00:32:32.270 align:middle line:84%
And all of this to be able--
because what you're doing

00:32:32.270 --> 00:32:35.600 align:middle line:84%
is almost getting kind of
alchemical transformation

00:32:35.600 --> 00:32:36.845 align:middle line:90%
in people.

00:32:36.845 --> 00:32:38.917 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: I don't mind
being called an alchemist.

00:32:38.917 --> 00:32:39.750 align:middle line:90%
I don't mind at all.

00:32:39.750 --> 00:32:40.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's what
it seems like to me.

00:32:40.970 --> 00:32:42.345 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: Because
homeopaths have

00:32:42.345 --> 00:32:44.150 align:middle line:84%
to have a very
intimate understanding

00:32:44.150 --> 00:32:45.570 align:middle line:90%
of these substances.

00:32:45.570 --> 00:32:48.980 align:middle line:84%
So almost like saying, I know
the consciousness of iron,

00:32:48.980 --> 00:32:50.900 align:middle line:84%
I know the consciousness
of aluminum.

00:32:50.900 --> 00:32:54.675 align:middle line:84%
Because I know when
people have gone

00:32:54.675 --> 00:32:57.050 align:middle line:84%
through a homeopathic proving
where they've ingested that

00:32:57.050 --> 00:32:59.670 align:middle line:84%
over a consistent period
of time, what mental,

00:32:59.670 --> 00:33:01.250 align:middle line:90%
emotional mindset is created.

00:33:01.250 --> 00:33:03.620 align:middle line:84%
And frankly, this goes
beyond what psychiatrists do.

00:33:03.620 --> 00:33:04.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Far beyond.

00:33:04.560 --> 00:33:05.810 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: Far and beyond that.

00:33:05.810 --> 00:33:07.685 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I don't mind being
called an alchemist.

00:33:07.685 --> 00:33:08.485 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:33:08.485 --> 00:33:10.047 align:middle line:84%
So Paracelsus, you
say that's kind

00:33:10.047 --> 00:33:11.630 align:middle line:84%
of where it started,
was an alchemist,

00:33:11.630 --> 00:33:13.430 align:middle line:90%
was noted as being alchemist.

00:33:13.430 --> 00:33:16.820 align:middle line:84%
So this is kind of baked
into the cake of homeopathy

00:33:16.820 --> 00:33:18.110 align:middle line:90%
if you're doing your job well.

00:33:18.110 --> 00:33:18.740 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: Yes.

00:33:18.740 --> 00:33:19.220 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:33:19.220 --> 00:33:19.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:33:19.610 --> 00:33:21.110 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: It's
really psychological.

00:33:21.110 --> 00:33:23.180 align:middle line:84%
It's probably the deepest
form of psychology

00:33:23.180 --> 00:33:24.740 align:middle line:90%
that you can possibly encounter.

00:33:24.740 --> 00:33:26.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, it's
absolutely fascinating.

00:33:26.690 --> 00:33:27.490 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:33:27.490 --> 00:33:32.030 align:middle line:84%
So now back in the day, let's
go to the case of Mary Lincoln

00:33:32.030 --> 00:33:34.310 align:middle line:84%
Todd because it's--
or Mary Todd Lincoln--

00:33:34.310 --> 00:33:37.490 align:middle line:90%
it's absolutely fascinating.

00:33:37.490 --> 00:33:40.370 align:middle line:84%
In history, they don't
treat her kindly basically

00:33:40.370 --> 00:33:43.980 align:middle line:84%
saying she was bat,
you know, crazy.

00:33:43.980 --> 00:33:46.280 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about what
was going on with her,

00:33:46.280 --> 00:33:48.080 align:middle line:84%
what the symptoms
were, and what happened

00:33:48.080 --> 00:33:51.680 align:middle line:84%
before and after her
husband's assassination,

00:33:51.680 --> 00:33:54.080 align:middle line:84%
and ultimately what
helped cure her.

00:33:54.080 --> 00:33:55.610 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: Yeah, this is a--

00:33:55.610 --> 00:33:58.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because they did
have these wonderful places

00:33:58.050 --> 00:33:58.850 align:middle line:90%
back then.

00:33:58.850 --> 00:34:00.808 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: This is a very
complex story, but I--

00:34:00.808 --> 00:34:01.933 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's fascinating.

00:34:01.933 --> 00:34:04.340 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: --I think I figured
something out about it.

00:34:04.340 --> 00:34:08.960 align:middle line:84%
Poor Mary Todd Lincoln,
she was from the south,

00:34:08.960 --> 00:34:13.190 align:middle line:84%
so she was a pariah in
Lincoln's White House

00:34:13.190 --> 00:34:16.040 align:middle line:84%
just being from the south,
her family had owned slaves.

00:34:16.040 --> 00:34:18.955 align:middle line:84%
She lost in-laws
in the Civil War.

00:34:18.955 --> 00:34:21.620 align:middle line:90%


00:34:21.620 --> 00:34:24.949 align:middle line:84%
She had a serious head injury
falling from a carriage.

00:34:24.949 --> 00:34:27.679 align:middle line:84%
She was trolled by
William Danforth, who

00:34:27.679 --> 00:34:31.250 align:middle line:84%
wrote these - this one
article that she was not

00:34:31.250 --> 00:34:32.489 align:middle line:90%
Lincoln's first love.

00:34:32.489 --> 00:34:33.739 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, he tortured her.

00:34:33.739 --> 00:34:35.822 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: And then, of
course, losing two children

00:34:35.822 --> 00:34:37.980 align:middle line:84%
and having her husband
murdered right next to her.

00:34:37.980 --> 00:34:39.860 align:middle line:90%
She went quite nuts.

00:34:39.860 --> 00:34:42.530 align:middle line:84%
And the accounts of
that are very graphic.

00:34:42.530 --> 00:34:46.010 align:middle line:84%
And her son, Robert Lincoln,
was worried about her.

00:34:46.010 --> 00:34:50.219 align:middle line:84%
And he decided she needed to
be treated or put someplace,

00:34:50.219 --> 00:34:51.540 align:middle line:90%
and she resisted this.

00:34:51.540 --> 00:34:54.320 align:middle line:84%
And so there was a trial,
a sensational trial

00:34:54.320 --> 00:34:55.790 align:middle line:90%
of her sanity.

00:34:55.790 --> 00:34:58.160 align:middle line:90%
14 doctors testified.

00:34:58.160 --> 00:35:01.190 align:middle line:84%
There was absolutely no question
that she was highly delusional.

00:35:01.190 --> 00:35:03.950 align:middle line:84%
She had thought there were wires
being pulled out of her eyes.

00:35:03.950 --> 00:35:07.440 align:middle line:84%
She thought that the city
of Chicago was burning down.

00:35:07.440 --> 00:35:09.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Totally lost her plot.

00:35:09.420 --> 00:35:10.220 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:35:10.220 --> 00:35:15.780 align:middle line:10%
>>KANTOR: She was completely
very delusional upset.

00:35:15.780 --> 00:35:17.250 align:middle line:90%
So yeah, she.

00:35:17.250 --> 00:35:22.255 align:middle line:84%
Was found incurably insane
and a number of the doctors

00:35:22.255 --> 00:35:24.630 align:middle line:84%
there on the panel-- a number
of them who were homeopaths

00:35:24.630 --> 00:35:29.520 align:middle line:84%
said, let's send it over
to Richard Patterson.

00:35:29.520 --> 00:35:32.910 align:middle line:84%
He's got a little
asylum in Bellevue,

00:35:32.910 --> 00:35:34.690 align:middle line:84%
Illinois called the
Batavia Institute.

00:35:34.690 --> 00:35:36.450 align:middle line:90%
Let's send her to him.

00:35:36.450 --> 00:35:38.320 align:middle line:90%
Now, what was curious about him?

00:35:38.320 --> 00:35:40.620 align:middle line:84%
He was a moral
care practitioner.

00:35:40.620 --> 00:35:46.110 align:middle line:84%
Moral care is a high level of
hand-holding, being respectful.

00:35:46.110 --> 00:35:48.612 align:middle line:90%
Officially no drugging at all.

00:35:48.612 --> 00:35:50.070 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's what
world care was.

00:35:50.070 --> 00:35:53.910 align:middle line:84%
So history gives us two stories
about Mary Todd Lincoln.

00:35:53.910 --> 00:35:56.280 align:middle line:84%
And they both are
equally preposterous.

00:35:56.280 --> 00:35:59.377 align:middle line:84%
One was, well, that
report about her madness,

00:35:59.377 --> 00:36:00.210 align:middle line:90%
that can't be right.

00:36:00.210 --> 00:36:02.130 align:middle line:84%
She was really never
crazy in the first place.

00:36:02.130 --> 00:36:03.180 align:middle line:90%
That's impossible.

00:36:03.180 --> 00:36:04.930 align:middle line:84%
The records speak
for themselves.

00:36:04.930 --> 00:36:09.270 align:middle line:84%
And the other one was, well,
OK, yeah, she was pretty upset.

00:36:09.270 --> 00:36:11.370 align:middle line:84%
And she just needed
some peace and quiet.

00:36:11.370 --> 00:36:14.587 align:middle line:84%
And then these two lawyers
got involved with her.

00:36:14.587 --> 00:36:15.420 align:middle line:90%
And they sprung her.

00:36:15.420 --> 00:36:16.950 align:middle line:90%
And that's what happened there.

00:36:16.950 --> 00:36:19.470 align:middle line:90%
Both accounts are ridiculous.

00:36:19.470 --> 00:36:22.260 align:middle line:84%
So I focused on what actually
happened at the Batavia

00:36:22.260 --> 00:36:23.970 align:middle line:84%
Institute with
Richard Patterson, who

00:36:23.970 --> 00:36:25.500 align:middle line:90%
was not officially a homeopath.

00:36:25.500 --> 00:36:26.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Officially?

00:36:26.070 --> 00:36:27.450 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: He was not
officially a homeopath.

00:36:27.450 --> 00:36:28.992 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You keep
saying officially.

00:36:28.992 --> 00:36:31.470 align:middle line:84%
>>KANTOR: Well, because
people did declare themselves.

00:36:31.470 --> 00:36:33.972 align:middle line:84%
At that time, it was still
a big paradigm bottle.

00:36:33.972 --> 00:36:36.180 align:middle line:84%
The homeopaths were making
all the money, by the way.

00:36:36.180 --> 00:36:39.150 align:middle line:84%
And the regular doctors
were annoyed by that.

00:36:39.150 --> 00:36:40.680 align:middle line:90%
That's why the AMA was formed.

00:36:40.680 --> 00:36:44.778 align:middle line:84%
If I was living in that time, I
might have been pretty wealthy.

00:36:44.778 --> 00:36:47.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Interesting because
the tables have certainly

00:36:47.070 --> 00:36:48.100 align:middle line:90%
reversed on that one.

00:36:48.100 --> 00:36:48.240 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: Yeah.

00:36:48.240 --> 00:36:50.290 align:middle line:84%
And I think the allopaths
have said, well,

00:36:50.290 --> 00:36:51.750 align:middle line:84%
we're never going to let
them eat our lunch again.

00:36:51.750 --> 00:36:53.520 align:middle line:84%
And that's never
going to happen again.

00:36:53.520 --> 00:36:56.460 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, these
homeopaths, they said,

00:36:56.460 --> 00:36:57.572 align:middle line:90%
go see Richard Patterson.

00:36:57.572 --> 00:36:58.530 align:middle line:90%
It was like wink, wink.

00:36:58.530 --> 00:36:59.490 align:middle line:90%
They knew something.

00:36:59.490 --> 00:37:02.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, Patterson, he was
a shrewd character.

00:37:02.340 --> 00:37:03.640 align:middle line:90%
He did not keep records.

00:37:03.640 --> 00:37:05.400 align:middle line:84%
But what I did
find out about him,

00:37:05.400 --> 00:37:07.410 align:middle line:84%
he used some remedies,
the medicines

00:37:07.410 --> 00:37:11.100 align:middle line:84%
that were popular at that
time, which is unquestionably

00:37:11.100 --> 00:37:12.330 align:middle line:90%
quoted for homeopathy.

00:37:12.330 --> 00:37:14.580 align:middle line:84%
That's the closest they
can come to admitting it.

00:37:14.580 --> 00:37:17.550 align:middle line:84%
His asylum, by the way,
opened almost exactly the time

00:37:17.550 --> 00:37:20.520 align:middle line:84%
that the Middletown Asylum
opened in Middletown, New York.

00:37:20.520 --> 00:37:22.680 align:middle line:84%
This was homeopathy at
its absolute zenith.

00:37:22.680 --> 00:37:25.890 align:middle line:84%
And there was poaching
across the borders.

00:37:25.890 --> 00:37:27.390 align:middle line:84%
People wanted to
help their clients,

00:37:27.390 --> 00:37:30.360 align:middle line:84%
and they had control over
how much of substance

00:37:30.360 --> 00:37:31.230 align:middle line:90%
would be used.

00:37:31.230 --> 00:37:33.900 align:middle line:84%
And the allopaths
were constantly

00:37:33.900 --> 00:37:38.370 align:middle line:84%
using homeopathic dosage
remedies but not admitting it.

00:37:38.370 --> 00:37:41.080 align:middle line:84%
And Patterson, I think, was
the perfect example of that.

00:37:41.080 --> 00:37:44.430 align:middle line:84%
In any case, within four
months, Mary Todd Lincoln

00:37:44.430 --> 00:37:46.800 align:middle line:84%
is sitting on his porch,
writing letters to her friends,

00:37:46.800 --> 00:37:49.920 align:middle line:84%
talking to his children,
just perfectly fine.

00:37:49.920 --> 00:37:51.745 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Not stark
raving mad anymore.

00:37:51.745 --> 00:37:52.050 align:middle line:90%
>>KANTOR: Not stark raving.

00:37:52.050 --> 00:37:53.550 align:middle line:84%
And then she was declared
with these lawyers

00:37:53.550 --> 00:37:54.758 align:middle line:90%
that declared perfectly sane.

00:37:54.758 --> 00:37:56.070 align:middle line:90%
She had many problems.

00:37:56.070 --> 00:37:58.875 align:middle line:84%
And I'm quite sure
